# P11-001: ATTACH a pfile as a catalog of views

Expose a PLINK fileset as an attachable "database" so a fileset reads like a
schema of tables — matching the mental model genomics users already have (a plink
fileset / Hail MatrixTable is one unit): `ATTACH 'cohort' AS c (TYPE plink)` →
`SELECT * FROM c.variants`, `c.samples`, `c.genotypes`, `c.freq`, ...

## Status

- [ ] Feasibility spike on DuckDB's storage/catalog extension API (biggest unknown)
- [ ] `plink_attach()` macro/view helper (cheap interim — validates demand)
- [ ] `ATTACH ... (TYPE plink)` catalog exposing per-orient + analysis views
- [ ] Read path; (later) write path once the writer exists
- [ ] Tests + docs

## Prerequisites

- **Benefits strongly from P10-001 (filter pushdown)** — without it the exposed
  views are rigid (a view can't take named params, so its flexibility comes from
  `WHERE` pushing down into region/sample/af filters). Do P10 first.
- **Write support depends on P9 (the pfile writer)** — a pfile is not a mutable
  catalog until then; attach is read-only initially.

## Branch

`feature/P11-001-attach-pfile-catalog`

